#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:131
msgid "KrausChannel"
msgstr "KrausChannel"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:133
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
":class:`~qilisdk.noise.representations.KrausChannel` is a base class for "
"digital noise models that use Kraus operators to represent quantum noise "
"channels. Kraus operators can be used to represent a generic quantum "
"channel :math:`\\mathcal{E}` acting on a density matrix :math:`\\rho` as:"
msgstr ""
":class:`~qilisdk.noise.representations.KrausChannel` és una classe base per "
"a models de soroll digital que utilitzen operadors de Kraus per representar "
"canals de soroll quàntic. Els operadors de Kraus es poden utilitzar per "
"representar un canal quàntic genèric :math:`\\mathcal{E}` que actua sobre "
"una matriu de densitat :math:`\\rho` com:"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:136
#, python-brace-format
msgid "\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = \\sum_i K_i \\rho K_i^\\dagger,"
msgstr "\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = \\sum_i K_i \\rho K_i^\\dagger,"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:140
msgid ""
"where :math:`K_i` are the Kraus operators satisfying the completeness "
"relation :math:`\\sum_i K_i^\\dagger K_i = I`. The class is initialized "
"with a list of Kraus operators given as QTensors."
msgstr ""
"on :math:`K_i` són els operadors de Kraus que satisfan la relació de "
"completesa :math:`\\sum_i K_i^\\dagger K_i = I`. La classe s'inicialitza "
"amb una llista d'operadors de Kraus donats com a QTensors."

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:154
msgid "LindbladGenerator"
msgstr "LindbladGenerator"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:156
msgid ""
":class:`~qilisdk.noise.representations.LindbladGenerator` is a base class"
" for analog noise models that use the Lindblad master equation to "
"represent quantum noise processes. The Lindblad master equation describes"
" the time evolution of a density matrix :math:`\\rho` under both unitary "
"dynamics and dissipative processes:"
msgstr ""
":class:`~qilisdk.noise.representations.LindbladGenerator` és una classe base "
"per a models de soroll analògic que utilitzen l'equació mestra de Lindblad "
"per representar processos de soroll quàntic. L'equació mestra de Lindblad "
"descriu l'evolució temporal d'una matriu de densitat :math:`\\rho` sota "
"dinàmiques unitàries i processos dissipatius:"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:160
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\frac{d\\rho}{dt} = -i[H, \\rho] + \\sum_i \\left( J_i \\rho "
"J_i^\\dagger - \\frac{1}{2} \\{ J_i^\\dagger J_i, \\rho \\} \\right),"
msgstr ""
"\\frac{d\\rho}{dt} = -i[H, \\rho] + \\sum_i \\left( J_i \\rho "
"J_i^\\dagger - \\frac{1}{2} \\{ J_i^\\dagger J_i, \\rho \\} \\right),"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:164
msgid ""
"where :math:`H` is the system Hamiltonian, and :math:`J_i` are the jump "
"operators representing different dissipation channels. The class is "
"initialized with a list of jump operators given as QTensors and their "
"corresponding rates (assumed to be 1 if not specified)."
msgstr ""
"on :math:`H` és el Hamiltonià del sistema, i :math:`J_i` són els operadors "
"de salt que representen diferents canals de dissipació. La classe "
"s'inicialitza amb una llista d'operadors de salt donats com a QTensors i les "
"seves taxes corresponents (s'assumeix que són 1 si no s'especifiquen)."

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:177
msgid "PauliChannel"
msgstr "PauliChannel"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:179
msgid ""
":class:`~qilisdk.noise.pauli_channel.PauliChannel` is a base class for "
"noise models that use Pauli operators. A Pauli channel applies the Pauli "
"operators (I, X, Y, Z) with certain probabilities. The channel can be "
"represented as:"
msgstr ""
":class:`~qilisdk.noise.pauli_channel.PauliChannel` és una classe base per a "
"models de soroll que utilitzen operadors de Pauli. Un canal de Pauli aplica "
"els operadors de Pauli (I, X, Y, Z) amb certes probabilitats. El canal es "
"pot representar com:"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:183
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = p_I \\rho + p_X X \\rho X + p_Y Y \\rho Y + p_Z Z "
"\\rho Z,"
msgstr ""
"\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = p_I \\rho + p_X X \\rho X + p_Y Y \\rho Y + p_Z Z "
"\\rho Z,"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:187
msgid ""
"where :math:`p_I`, :math:`p_X`, :math:`p_Y`, and :math:`p_Z` are the "
"probabilities for applying the respective Pauli operators, satisfying "
":math:`p_I + p_X + p_Y + p_Z = 1`. This corresponds to Kraus operators:"
msgstr ""
"on :math:`p_I`, :math:`p_X`, :math:`p_Y` i :math:`p_Z` són les "
"probabilitats d'aplicar els respectius operadors de Pauli, satisfent "
":math:`p_I + p_X + p_Y + p_Z = 1`. Això correspon als operadors de Kraus:"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:191
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"K_0 = \\sqrt{p_I} I, \\quad K_1 = \\sqrt{p_X} X, \\quad K_2 = \\sqrt{p_Y}"
" Y, \\quad K_3 = \\sqrt{p_Z} Z,"
msgstr ""
"K_0 = \\sqrt{p_I} I, \\quad K_1 = \\sqrt{p_X} X, \\quad K_2 = \\sqrt{p_Y}"
" Y, \\quad K_3 = \\sqrt{p_Z} Z,"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:195
msgid "Or jump operators:"
msgstr "O com a operadors de salt:"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:197
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"J_1 = \\sqrt{\\gamma_X} X, \\quad J_2 = \\sqrt{\\gamma_Y} Y, \\quad J_3 ="
" \\sqrt{\\gamma_Z} Z,"
msgstr ""
"J_1 = \\sqrt{\\gamma_X} X, \\quad J_2 = \\sqrt{\\gamma_Y} Y, \\quad J_3 ="
" \\sqrt{\\gamma_Z} Z,"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:201
msgid "where :math:`\\gamma_i` are rates related to the probabilities."
msgstr "on :math:`\\gamma_i` són taxes relacionades amb les probabilitats."

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:209
msgid "BitFlip"
msgstr "BitFlip"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:211
msgid ""
":class:`~qilisdk.noise.bit_flip.BitFlip` represents a bit-flip error "
"model where each qubit has a certain probability of flipping its state "
"from :math:`|0⟩` to :math:`|1⟩` or from :math:`|1⟩` to :math:`|0⟩`. This "
"corresponds to the following channel:"
msgstr ""
":class:`~qilisdk.noise.bit_flip.BitFlip` representa un model d'error "
"d'inversió de bit on cada qubit té una certa probabilitat d'invertir el seu "
"estat de :math:`|0⟩` a :math:`|1⟩` o de :math:`|1⟩` a :math:`|0⟩`. Això "
"correspon al canal següent:"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:215
#, python-brace-format
msgid "\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = (1 - p) \\rho + p X \\rho X,"
msgstr "\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = (1 - p) \\rho + p X \\rho X,"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:219
msgid ""
"where :math:`p` is the bit-flip probability. As such, it is a special "
"case of :class:`~qilisdk.noise.pauli_channel.PauliChannel` with "
":math:`p_X = p` and :math:`p_I = 1 - p`. This can therefore be written as"
" Kraus operators:"
msgstr ""
"on :math:`p` és la probabilitat d'inversió de bit. Com a tal, és un cas "
"especial de :class:`~qilisdk.noise.pauli_channel.PauliChannel` amb "
":math:`p_X = p` i :math:`p_I = 1 - p`. Per tant, es pot escriure com a "
"operadors de Kraus:"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:222
#, python-brace-format
msgid "K_0 = \\sqrt{1 - p} I, \\quad K_1 = \\sqrt{p} X,"
msgstr "K_0 = \\sqrt{1 - p} I, \\quad K_1 = \\sqrt{p} X,"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:226
#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:257
#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:357
msgid "or similarly as a jump operator:"
msgstr "o de manera similar com a operador de salt:"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:228
#, python-brace-format
msgid "J = \\sqrt{\\gamma} X,"
msgstr "J = \\sqrt{\\gamma} X,"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:232
msgid "where now :math:`\\gamma` is the bit-flip rate."
msgstr "on ara :math:`\\gamma` és la taxa d'inversió de bit."

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:240
msgid "PhaseFlip"
msgstr "PhaseFlip"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:242
msgid ""
":class:`~qilisdk.noise.phase_flip.PhaseFlip` represents a phase-flip "
"error model where each qubit has a certain probability of flipping its "
"phase, changing the sign of the :math:`|1⟩` state. This corresponds to "
"the following channel:"
msgstr ""
":class:`~qilisdk.noise.phase_flip.PhaseFlip` representa un model d'error "
"d'inversió de fase on cada qubit té una certa probabilitat d'invertir la "
"seva fase, canviant el signe de l'estat :math:`|1⟩`. Això correspon al "
"canal següent:"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:246
#, python-brace-format
msgid "\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = (1 - p) \\rho + p Z \\rho Z,"
msgstr "\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = (1 - p) \\rho + p Z \\rho Z,"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:250
msgid ""
"where :math:`p` is the phase-flip probability. As such, it is a special "
"case of :class:`~qilisdk.noise.pauli_channel.PauliChannel` with "
":math:`p_Z = p` and :math:`p_I = 1 - p`. This can therefore be written as"
" Kraus operators:"
msgstr ""
"on :math:`p` és la probabilitat d'inversió de fase. Com a tal, és un cas "
"especial de :class:`~qilisdk.noise.pauli_channel.PauliChannel` amb "
":math:`p_Z = p` i :math:`p_I = 1 - p`. Per tant, es pot escriure com a "
"operadors de Kraus:"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:253
#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:353
#, python-brace-format
msgid "K_0 = \\sqrt{1 - p} I, \\quad K_1 = \\sqrt{p} Z,"
msgstr "K_0 = \\sqrt{1 - p} I, \\quad K_1 = \\sqrt{p} Z,"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:259
#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:359
#, python-brace-format
msgid "J = \\sqrt{\\gamma} Z,"
msgstr "J = \\sqrt{\\gamma} Z,"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:263
msgid "where now :math:`\\gamma` is the phase-flip rate."
msgstr "on ara :math:`\\gamma` és la taxa d'inversió de fase."

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:271
msgid "Depolarizing"
msgstr "Depolarizing"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:273
msgid ""
":class:`~qilisdk.noise.depolarizing.Depolarizing` represents a "
"depolarizing error model where each qubit has a certain probability of "
"being replaced by the maximally mixed state. This corresponds to the "
"following channel:"
msgstr ""
":class:`~qilisdk.noise.depolarizing.Depolarizing` representa un model "
"d'error despolaritzant on cada qubit té una certa probabilitat de ser "
"substituït per l'estat màximament mesclat. Això correspon al canal següent:"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:277
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = (1 - p) \\rho + \\frac{p}{3} (X \\rho X + Y \\rho Y"
" + Z \\rho Z),"
msgstr ""
"\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = (1 - p) \\rho + \\frac{p}{3} (X \\rho X + Y \\rho Y"
" + Z \\rho Z),"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:281
msgid ""
"where :math:`p` is the depolarizing probability. As such, it is a special"
" case of :class:`~qilisdk.noise.pauli_channel.PauliChannel` with "
":math:`p_X = p_Y = p_Z = p/3` and :math:`p_I = 1 - p`. This can therefore"
" be written as Kraus operators:"
msgstr ""
"on :math:`p` és la probabilitat de despolarització. Com a tal, és un cas "
"especial de :class:`~qilisdk.noise.pauli_channel.PauliChannel` amb "
":math:`p_X = p_Y = p_Z = p/3` i :math:`p_I = 1 - p`. Per tant, es pot "
"escriure com a operadors de Kraus:"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:284
msgid ""
"K_0 = \\sqrt{1 - p} I, \\quad K_1 = \\sqrt{\\frac{p}{3}} X, \\quad K_2 = "
"\\sqrt{\\frac{p}{3}} Y, \\quad K_3 = \\sqrt{\\frac{p}{3}} Z,"
msgstr ""
"K_0 = \\sqrt{1 - p} I, \\quad K_1 = \\sqrt{\\frac{p}{3}} X, \\quad K_2 = "
"\\sqrt{\\frac{p}{3}} Y, \\quad K_3 = \\sqrt{\\frac{p}{3}} Z,"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:288
msgid "or similarly as jump operators:"
msgstr "o de manera similar com a operadors de salt:"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:290
msgid ""
"J_1 = \\sqrt{\\frac{\\gamma}{3}} X, \\quad J_2 = "
"\\sqrt{\\frac{\\gamma}{3}} Y, \\quad J_3 = \\sqrt{\\frac{\\gamma}{3}} Z,"
msgstr ""
"J_1 = \\sqrt{\\frac{\\gamma}{3}} X, \\quad J_2 = "
"\\sqrt{\\frac{\\gamma}{3}} Y, \\quad J_3 = \\sqrt{\\frac{\\gamma}{3}} Z,"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:294
msgid "where :math:`\\gamma` is the depolarizing rate."
msgstr "on :math:`\\gamma` és la taxa de despolarització."

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:302
msgid "AmplitudeDamping"
msgstr "AmplitudeDamping"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:304
msgid ""
":class:`~qilisdk.noise.amplitude_damping.AmplitudeDamping` represents an "
"amplitude damping error model where each qubit has a certain probability "
"of decaying from the excited state :math:`|1⟩` to the ground state "
":math:`|0⟩`. This corresponds to the following channel:"
msgstr ""
":class:`~qilisdk.noise.amplitude_damping.AmplitudeDamping` representa un "
"model d'error d'amortiment d'amplitud on cada qubit té una certa probabilitat "
"de decaure de l'estat excitat :math:`|1⟩` a l'estat fonamental :math:`|0⟩`. "
"Això correspon al canal següent:"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:308
#, python-brace-format
msgid "\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = E_0 \\rho E_0^\\dagger + E_1 \\rho E_1^\\dagger."
msgstr "\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = E_0 \\rho E_0^\\dagger + E_1 \\rho E_1^\\dagger."

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:312
msgid "Here the Kraus operators are defined as:"
msgstr "Aquí els operadors de Kraus es defineixen com:"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:314
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"E_0 = \\begin{pmatrix} 1 & 0 \\\\ 0 & \\sqrt{1 - p} \\end{pmatrix}, "
"\\quad E_1 = \\begin{pmatrix} 0 & \\sqrt{p} \\\\ 0 & 0 \\end{pmatrix},"
msgstr ""
"E_0 = \\begin{pmatrix} 1 & 0 \\\\ 0 & \\sqrt{1 - p} \\end{pmatrix}, "
"\\quad E_1 = \\begin{pmatrix} 0 & \\sqrt{p} \\\\ 0 & 0 \\end{pmatrix},"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:318
msgid ""
"where :math:`p` is the amplitude damping probability. The channel can "
"also be represented using the jump operator:"
msgstr ""
"on :math:`p` és la probabilitat d'amortiment d'amplitud. El canal també es "
"pot representar utilitzant l'operador de salt:"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:320
#, python-brace-format
msgid "J = \\sqrt{\\gamma} \\sigma_-,"
msgstr "J = \\sqrt{\\gamma} \\sigma_-,"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:324
msgid ""
"where :math:`\\gamma` is the amplitude damping rate and :math:`\\sigma_-`"
" is the lowering operator. The channel is defined by the :math:`T_1` time"
" constant, with the relations:"
msgstr ""
"on :math:`\\gamma` és la taxa d'amortiment d'amplitud i :math:`\\sigma_-` "
"és l'operador d'abaixament. El canal es defineix per la constant de temps "
":math:`T_1`, amb les relacions:"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:327
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"p = 1 - e^{-t / T_1},\n"
"\\gamma = \\frac{1}{T_1},"
msgstr ""
"p = 1 - e^{-t / T_1},\n"
"\\gamma = \\frac{1}{T_1},"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:332
msgid ""
"where :math:`t` is the time duration over which the amplitude damping "
"occurs."
msgstr ""
"on :math:`t` és la durada temporal sobre la qual es produeix l'amortiment "
"d'amplitud."

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:340
msgid "Dephasing"
msgstr "Dephasing"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:342
msgid ""
":class:`~qilisdk.noise.dephasing.Dephasing` represents a dephasing error "
"model where each qubit has a certain probability of losing coherence "
"between its :math:`|0⟩` and :math:`|1⟩` states. This corresponds to the "
"following channel:"
msgstr ""
":class:`~qilisdk.noise.dephasing.Dephasing` representa un model d'error de "
"desfasament on cada qubit té una certa probabilitat de perdre coherència "
"entre els seus estats :math:`|0⟩` i :math:`|1⟩`. Això correspon al canal "
"següent:"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:346
#, python-brace-format
msgid "\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = (1 - p) \\rho + p Z \\rho Z"
msgstr "\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = (1 - p) \\rho + p Z \\rho Z"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:350
msgid ""
"where :math:`p` is the dephasing probability. As such, it is a special "
"case of :class:`~qilisdk.noise.pauli_channel.PauliChannel` with "
":math:`p_Z = p` and :math:`p_I = 1 - p`. This can therefore be written as"
" Kraus operators:"
msgstr ""
"on :math:`p` és la probabilitat de desfasament. Com a tal, és un cas "
"especial de :class:`~qilisdk.noise.pauli_channel.PauliChannel` amb "
":math:`p_Z = p` i :math:`p_I = 1 - p`. Per tant, es pot escriure com a "
"operadors de Kraus:"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:363
msgid ""
"where now :math:`\\gamma` is the dephasing rate. The channel is defined "
"by the :math:`T_\\phi` time constant, with the relations:"
msgstr ""
"on ara :math:`\\gamma` és la taxa de desfasament. El canal es defineix per "
"la constant de temps :math:`T_\\phi`, amb les relacions:"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:365
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"p = \\frac{1}{2} \\left( 1 - e^{-t / T_\\phi} \\right),\n"
"\\gamma = \\frac{1}{T_\\phi},"
msgstr ""
"p = \\frac{1}{2} \\left( 1 - e^{-t / T_\\phi} \\right),\n"
"\\gamma = \\frac{1}{T_\\phi},"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:370
msgid "where :math:`t` is the time duration over which the dephasing occurs."
msgstr "on :math:`t` és la durada temporal sobre la qual es produeix el desfasament."

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:379
msgid "GaussianPerturbation"
msgstr "GaussianPerturbation"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:381
msgid ""
":class:`~qilisdk.noise.gaussian_perturbation.GaussianPerturbation` "
"represents a noise model that adds Gaussian-distributed perturbations to "
"the parameters of gates or Hamiltonian terms in a quantum circuit or "
"schedule. This simulates imperfections in control signals that can lead "
"to deviations from the intended operations. The perturbations are drawn "
"from a Gaussian distribution with a specified standard deviation:"
msgstr ""
":class:`~qilisdk.noise.gaussian_perturbation.GaussianPerturbation` "
"representa un model de soroll que afegeix pertorbacions distribuïdes "
"gaussianament als paràmetres de les portes o dels termes del Hamiltonià en "
"un circuit quàntic o esquema. Això simula imperfeccions en els senyals de "
"control que poden conduir a desviacions de les operacions previstes. Les "
"pertorbacions es prenen d'una distribució gaussiana amb una desviació "
"estàndard especificada:"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:386
#, python-brace-format
msgid "\\delta \\theta \\sim \\mathcal{N}(\\mu, \\sigma^2),"
msgstr "\\delta \\theta \\sim \\mathcal{N}(\\mu, \\sigma^2),"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:390
msgid ""
"where :math:`\\sigma` is the standard deviation of the perturbations and "
":math:`\\mu` is the mean (defaulting to 0)."
msgstr ""
"on :math:`\\sigma` és la desviació estàndard de les pertorbacions i "
":math:`\\mu` és la mitjana (per defecte 0)."

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:398
msgid "OffsetPerturbation"
msgstr "OffsetPerturbation"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:399
msgid ""
":class:`~qilisdk.noise.offset_perturbation.OffsetPerturbation` represents"
" a noise model that adds fixed offset perturbations to the parameters of "
"gates or Hamiltonian terms in a quantum circuit or schedule. This "
"simulates systematic errors in control signals that consistently shift "
"the intended operations. The offsets are specified as fixed values for "
"each parameter."
msgstr ""
":class:`~qilisdk.noise.offset_perturbation.OffsetPerturbation` representa "
"un model de soroll que afegeix pertorbacions de desplaçament fixes als "
"paràmetres de les portes o dels termes del Hamiltonià en un circuit quàntic "
"o esquema. Això simula errors sistemàtics en els senyals de control que "
"desplacen consistentment les operacions previstes. Els desplaçaments "
"s'especifiquen com a valors fixos per a cada paràmetre."

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:410
msgid "ReadoutAssignment"
msgstr "ReadoutAssignment"

#: ../../modules/noise_models/noise_models.rst:412
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
":class:`~qilisdk.noise.readout_assignment.ReadoutAssignment` represents a"
" readout error model that simulates imperfections in the measurement "
"process of qubits. It is defined by two probabilities: the probability of"
" misreading a :math:`|0⟩` state as :math:`|1⟩` (:math:`p_{0 \\to 1}`) and"
" the probability of misreading a :math:`|1⟩` state as :math:`|0⟩` "
"(:math:`p_{1 \\to 0}`)."
msgstr ""
":class:`~qilisdk.noise.readout_assignment.ReadoutAssignment` representa un "
"model d'error de lectura que simula imperfeccions en el procés de mesura dels "
"qubits. Es defineix per dues probabilitats: la probabilitat de llegir "
"malament un estat :math:`|0⟩` com a :math:`|1⟩` (:math:`p_{0 \\to 1}`) i "
"la probabilitat de llegir malament un estat :math:`|1⟩` com a :math:`|0⟩` "
"(:math:`p_{1 \\to 0}`)."
